Subject: Re: [T2] Difference between 2 liter and 1800 cranks?

On Wed, Jul 23, 2003 at 05:29:11AM -0400, Vanagon Man wrote:
> wondering.I knew the rods and bore were different, but are the crankshafts
> the same?

sorta. the 2000 cranks are the same crank except for one difference.
the rod journals are turned down more (IIRC 5mm). and the center of
the journal is moved out from the main journal centerline. So in
effect they moved the cl of the rods out to give more stroke but kept
the same crank.

